ing a reliable and practical family vehicle. While newer models offer more modern features, the 2nd generation Pilot (2009-2015) is still sought after for its robust design and proven track record. The estimated value of $8,500 USD reflects a balance between its desirable features and its age, mileage, and condition. For reference, similar models in \'good\' condition with lower mileage might fetch $10,000-$13,000, while those in \'excellent\' condition with very low mileage could exceed $14,000. Recommendations for the seller include addressing the scratch on the rear bumper, as even minor cosmetic repairs can improve buyer perception and potentially increase the selling price. A thorough detailing of both the exterior and interior would also be beneficial. Providing a comprehensive service history will instill confidence in potential buyers, especially given the high mileage. Highlighting the AWD capability and Touring trim features in the listing will attract buyers looking for those specific options.','The provided images show a 2015 Honda Pilot Touring AWD in a dark red/burgundy metallic paint. The exterior appears to be in fair condition, consistent with the seller\'s description and the vehicle\'s age and mileage. There are visible reflections on the paint, indicating it has been recently washed, but also highlighting some surface imperfections. The most notable issue is a scratch or scuff mark on the lower passenger side of the rear bumper, as mentioned by the seller. This scratch is clearly visible in the cropped image focusing on the rear bumper. The paint finish otherwise appears to have a decent luster, though minor swirls or light scratches typical of a used vehicle are likely present upon closer inspection. The wheels are factory alloy wheels, showing some signs of use but no major curb rash or damage is immediately apparent. The tires appear to have reasonable tread depth, but their exact condition (age, brand, wear pattern) cannot be fully assessed f