ons for Seller\nFor the seller, a thorough detailing (interior and exterior) would be beneficial to maximize visual appeal. Address any minor cosmetic flaws or mechanical issues that fall within the \'fair\' condition description to improve perceived value. Gather all service records to demonstrate consistent maintenance, which is crucial for a high-mileage vehicle. Highlight any premium features or recent maintenance. Be prepared for negotiations, as buyers will likely focus on the mileage. Consider a pre-purchase inspection report to build buyer confidence. Pricing competitively within the stated range, perhaps starting closer to the higher end and being flexible, would be a good strategy.','Based on the provided images, the exterior appears to be in generally good condition for its age and stated \'fair\' condition, with a clean paint finish and no immediately visible major dents or scratches. The wheels look well-maintained. The headlights are clear, which is good. However, without interior images or detailed close-ups of all body panels, tires, and undercarriage, a comprehensive assessment is limited. The \'fair\' condition description suggests there might be minor cosmetic imperfections or mechanical issues not visible in the provided exterior shots.','2026-04-07 21:43:46'),(270002,1560039,NULL,'Honda','Pilot',2013,150000,'fair',9000.00,'USD','## Valuation Analysis for 2013 Honda Pilot\n\n### Estimated Market Value\n**USD 9,000**\n\nPrice Range: USD 8,000 - 10,500\n\n### Valuation Factors\nThe 2013 Honda Pilot is a popular mid-size SUV known for its reliability, spacious interior, and family-friendly features. The \'Touring\' trim, visible in the image, is the top-tier model, which includes premium features like navigation, leather seats, and a rear entertainment system (though not confirmed by images), adding to its value. The mileage of 150,000 km (approximately 93,200 miles) is moderate for a 2013 vehicle, indicating regular use but not excessively high. Ho