sclosure and preventing surprises during a buyer\'s inspection. Price competitively within the local market for similar 2013 Honda Pilot Touring 4WD models with comparable mileage and condition.','Based on the provided images and the \'fair\' condition description, the exterior appears to be in generally good shape for its age and mileage. The paint has a good shine, suggesting it has been cared for. There are some visible scratches on the rear bumper, particularly on the lower plastic trim and potentially on the painted section below the tailgate, which is consistent with a \'fair\' rating. The tires appear to have decent tread, and the alloy wheels show minor wear but no significant damage. The body panels look straight with no obvious dents or major rust visible. The \'Touring\' and \'4WD\' badges are present, confirming the trim level and drivetrain. The roof rails and running boards are also visible, adding to the utility and appearance. Without interior images or mechanical inspection, a full assessment is limited, but the exterior suggests a vehicle that has been used but not neglected.','2026-04-07 21:46:25'),(300001,1560039,NULL,'Honda','Pilot',2013,150000,'fair',8500.00,'USD','## Valuation Analysis for 2013 Honda Pilot\n\n### Estimated Market Value\n**USD 8,500**\n\nPrice Range: USD 7,500 - 9,500\n\n### Valuation Factors\nThe valuation is based on the vehicle being a 2013 Honda Pilot with 150,000 kilometers (approximately 93,200 miles). Key factors include the vehicle\'s age, mileage, and the \'Touring AWD\' trim level indicated by the badge, which is a higher-end trim. Honda\'s reputation for reliability and the Pilot\'s strong resale value in the SUV segment are positive factors. However, the \'fair\' condition assessment, including visible scratches and wear, and the age of the vehicle, contribute to depreciation. The market demand for used SUVs in this price range also plays a role.\n\n\n\n### Condition Assessment\nBased on the provided images and the 