inor curb rash visible. The body panels appear straight with no major dents evident from the angles provided. The chrome accents and roof rails are present and appear intact. The \'Touring AWD\' badge is visible, indicating a higher trim level.','2026-04-07 22:22:18'),(330001,450001,NULL,'KIA','RIO',2017,150000,'good',7500.00,'USD','{\"minPrice\":6800,\"maxPrice\":8200,\"factors\":\"The valuation for this 2017 KIA RIO with 150,000 kilometers is primarily influenced by its age, mileage, and reported \'good\' condition. KIA RIOs are known for their reliability and fuel efficiency, making them attractive in the used car market. However, 150,000 kilometers is a relatively high mileage for a 2017 model, which will depress the value compared to lower mileage examples. The \'good\' condition suggests no significant cosmetic or mechanical issues, which helps maintain its value. Market demand for compact, economical cars also plays a role.\",\"recommendations\":\"For the seller, it is recommended to compile a complete service history to demonstrate consistent maintenance, which can justify a higher price. Highlight the car\'s fuel efficiency and reliability in the listing. Professional detailing of both the interior and exterior will significantly enhance its appeal. Address any minor cosmetic imperfections or small repairs before listing. When setting the price, be prepared to negotiate, as the higher mileage might be a point of contention for potential buyers. Consider offering a pre-purchase inspection report to build buyer confidence.\"}','Based on the provided information stating \'good\' condition, it is assumed that the vehicle has no major dents, scratches, or rust on the exterior. The interior is likely clean and well-maintained with minimal wear and tear. Mechanically, it is presumed to be in sound working order, with all major components functioning correctly and no immediate need for significant repairs. Regular maintenance records, if available, would further support this assessment.','2026-04-09 21:27:32'),(330002,450001,NULL,'KIA','RIO',2017,150000,'good',8500.00,'USD','{\"minPrice\":7800,\"maxPrice\":9200,\"factors\":\"The valuation for the 2017 KIA RIO with 150,000 kilometers is primarily influenced by its age, mileage, and reported \'good\' condition. KIA RIOs are known for their reliability and fuel efficiency, making them popular in the used car market. However, 150,000 kilometers is considered high mileage for a 2017 model, which significantly impacts its value. The \'good\' condition helps maintain a reasonable price, assuming no major mechanical issues or significant cosmetic damage. Market demand for compact, economical vehicles also plays a role, generally keeping prices stable for well-maintained examples.\",\"recommendations\":\"For the seller, it is recommended to obtain a professional pre-sale inspection to identify any minor issues that could be addressed to enhance value and buyer confidence. Thoroughly clean and detail the car, both interior and exterior. Gather all service records to demonstrate a history of regular maintenance, which can justify the mileage. Highlight features such as fuel economy, reliability, and any recent maintenance or tire replacements. When listing, take high-quality photos from multiple angles, including the interior, engine bay, and odometer. Be transparent about the vehicle\'s history and any known imperfections.\"}','Based solely on the provided text description of \'good\' condition, it is assumed the vehicle has no major mechanical faults, the interior and exterior show only minor wear consistent with its age and mileage, and all primary functions are operational. Without images or a detailed inspection report, a more precise assessment is not possible.','2026-04-09 21:28:00'),(330003,450001,NULL,'Honda','Accord',1988,200000,'poor',1000.00,'USD','{\"minPrice\":500,\"maxPrice\":1500,\"factors\":\"The 1988 Honda Accord is a classic model, but its age (36 years old) and high 